<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>l. 1, The honorand is probably Apollonios Papias  <xref type="iAph">1335</xref> (=64.235), perhaps the brother of the donor in <xref type="iAph">1257</xref> (=MAMA 449, under Domitian) and of the honorand in <xref type="iAph">1765</xref> (=CIG 2766). The restoration of the statues, which is apparently referred to again in <xref type="iAph">564</xref>, was perhaps after the Trajanic earthquake. The same group apparently reappears in an inscription at Plarasa (Paton), where Secundus has become P. Aelius Secundus.</p>
<p>The singular verb with the plural subject is common in these texts.</p>
</div>
